body.plain: This Song is about Arnaud Rebotini’s young years as a teen/young adult and how he did many bad things like the frequent use of drug that he regrets now…

songs.lyrics:
I've got a bad habits I can't quit
And it's killing me
I'm a man in zero gravity
I said: "Docta, docta! Help me!"
I'm a sinner, a junker
And i'm a country boy...

[Verse 1: Arnaud Rebotini]
Boogie in zero gravity
Boogie in zero gravity

When I was younger
I wanna live with no boundaries
I couldn't keep the balance beyond good and evil
I never find my place, the right place
I'm a sinner, a junker
And i'm a country boy...

[Verse 2: Arnaud Rebotini]
Boogie in zero gravity
Boogie in zero gravity

songs.lyrics:
Now, when I was a little boy
At the age of five
I had somethin' in my pocket
Keeps a lot of folks alive

Now I'm a man
Turnin' twenty-one
You know, baby
We can have a lot of fun

I'm a man
I spell M-A-N
Woah, I'm a man

All you pretty women
Standin' in line
I can make a love to you, baby
In an hour's time

I'm a man
I spell M-A-N
Woah, I'm a man

Goin' back down
To Kansas town
To bring back the second cousin
Little Johnny the Conqueroo

I'm a man
I spell M-A-N
Woah, I'm a man

The line I shoot
Will never miss
The way I make love to 'em
They can't resist

I'm a man
I spell M-A-N
Woah, I'm a man

Woah, I'm a man
